
[1]baste

   BASTE, v.t.

   1. To beat with a stick.

   2. To drip butter or fat upon meat, as it turns upon the spit,in
   roasting; to moisten with fat or other liquid.

           BASTE, v.t. To sew with long stitches; to sew slightly.
